      "visualKind": "shape",
      "title": "<p><strong>Hi, it&#39;s Cat aka </strong><strong style=\"color:rgb(28,28,30)\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/askcatgpt/\">CatGPT</a>! </strong></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>Back in July 2025, I launched <strong style=\"color:rgb(28,28,30)\"><a href=\"https://physicalphones.com/?fbclid&#61;PAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQMMjU2MjgxMDQwNTU4AAGnsJPyT3n-G9pVguO9H99nzxcqjbVdaza3B7JwmKcHdeF4g5h1tt981JNH-5s_aem_djjiWzLUWoVHAz_tH2TuiA\">Physical Phones</a></strong>, a line of Bluetooth-compatible landlines that bring back focus, fun, and a little nostalgia.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>There’s a <em>lot </em>to be done to bring this vision and product to life. </strong>Every Friday, our team gathers for our weekly retro meeting where we reflect on what we accomplished in the last week and what we could have improved on. <strong>Notes are meant to be messy! Sticky notes! Word vomit! </strong></p><p><br /></p><p>But as a founder, I want to make sure when we say we could have done better, we <em>actually</em> change our behavior and DO better. <strong>So, to help, I created this Flow with Miro </strong>— and you can download this template to conduct your own retro and gather insights!</p><p><br /></p><p>After each meeting, I kick off this Flow and it summarizes our discussion into something easily readable and trackable. That way, I can revisit this and easily see if we’re making progress. </p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Here’s how to give it a try yourself → <br /></strong><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>"
    },
